Product Name: Dometic Mobicool MT38W ACDC Thermoelectric Portable Camping Coolbox
Product Description:
Dometic Mobicool MT38 AC/DC Thermoelectric Mobicool Cool Box

Ideal for picnics and camping trips to keep pre-chilled food and drink cool.

The Waeco MT38 Thermoelectric Cool Box has a capacity of 37 litres which can be run from either 12v DC or 230v AC. The MT38W can be used with the door in either top or front opening positions.

As well as being able to keep goods cool up to 18°C below the ambient temperature.

With the capacity to conveniently store 2 litre bottles vertically alongside an easily accessible door-in-door bottle compartment, the Mobicool MT38 Thermoelectric Mobicool Cool Box is optimised for easy, quick, convenience. 

Mobicool MT38W Thermoelectric Cool Box features:

  • Dual voltage, auto switch with integrated ABS active battery security
  • Multi - functional pull-out handle for convenient transport
  • Easy access door-in-door bottle compartment
  • Removable divider grid for easy organisation
  • Fits 2 litre bottles standing
  • Works both upright and lying
  • Hinged lid with quick lock system
  • Double fan system
  • The MT38 now comes with redesigned, robust wheels!

Product Name: Dometic Waeco Mobicool W48 Electric 12v Mains Portable Cool Box
Product Description:
Dometic Waeco W48 Mobicool Thermoelectric Portable Cooler

 

The largest thermoelectric coolbox available from Dometic-Waeco

With a full 48 litres of storage the Waeco W48 can be connected up to either a 12 Volt, ( Min 4 amps, ) power socket or 240 Volt mains. Both leads are supplied with the Waeco W48 Thermoelectric Cool Box.

The Waeco W48 Mobicool Cool Box is the biggest thermoelectric powered coolbox available and is completely at the top of it's game. The W48 is ideal for a number of occasions including overnight trips, big picnics, days at the beach, or taking already chilled food and drinks down to your Caravan or Boat.

A flexible handle system and wheels enable the Waeco W48 Thermoelectric Cool Box to be carried or used like a trolley which is handy when the whole 48 litres is used fully! And with a cooling capacity of up to 18 deg C below the ambient temperature as well as twin lids that provide easy access to either compartment when using the included internal divider, the Waeco W48 Mobicool Thermoelectric Cool Box is a convenient, easy to use and transportable high performance cooler.

Dometic Waeco W48 Mobicool Cool Box Features:

  • Multi function pull out handle
  • Dual voltage auto switch
  • Cooling to 20°C below ambient
  • 100% CFC free
  • Accommodates standing 2L bottles
  • Integrated cable compartment

Product Name: Dometic Waeco Mobicool Q40 Thermolectric 12v/240v Coolbox
Product Description:
Dometic Waeco Mobicool Q40 Electric Portable Cool Box

The Waeco Mobicool Q40 is a 40 litre cool box which can be run from either the 12 volt cigar lighter socket, ( min 4 amps. ) in your vehicle and also mains, which makes it an ideal choice for overnight camping, picnics and for transporting foods which must be kept chilled.

The Aluminium outer casing of the Waeco Mobicool Q40 Cool Box helps the cooler to achieve cooling down to 22°C below ambient temperature and assists with insulation within the box, keeping the cold in and any heat out.

The Waeco Mobicool Q40 also has a split lid design which ensures no unnecessary loss of cooling, with organised dividers so that food can be stored in one half and drinks in the other, ultimately enabling you to just open the side you want.

The Waeco Mobicool Q40 Cool Box also has a convenient cable storage compartment with a swinging cover to prevent trailing wires when the box is not being used.

 

Dometic Waeco Mobicool Q40 Cool Box Features

  • Car and indoor use with dual voltage system
  • Auto-switch
  • Sturdy
  • Unbreakable aluminium housing
  • Fold-away side handles
  • Split lid minimize cold loss
  • Cable compartment in lid
  • Fits 2-litre bottles standing
  • 2 removable divider grids
  • Double fan system

Product Name: Dometic Waeco Tropicool TCX14 Thermoelectric Cool Box
Product Description:
Dometic Waeco Tropicool TCX14 Thermoelectric 12/24v Cool Box

Excellent compact cooling of prechilled food or drinks, with a useful heat facility, ideal for keeping takeaways piping hot!

The Waeco Tropicool TCX 14 is a great 14 litre coolbox powered by the ‘Peltier’ thermoelectric system which basically means it can cool down as well as heat up! The same systems are wear free so are very reliable.

The TCX 14 can be run on 12/24 volts as standard, as well as mains for an all round coolbox, whether it’s for a dinner party to keep the wine cold or a day trip out with the family the TCX 14 will keep your food hot or your drinks cold all through the day.

Furthermore, the TCX 14 has a power save circuit with an integrated mains supply which can recognize where the power is coming from whether it be 12V or mains. This prioritises mains when it's available.

Dometic Waeco TCX14 Cool Box Features:

  • Capacity 14 litres
  • Adjustable variable point thermostat
  • Cooling and warming sliding
  • 12/24 volt DC car & AC mains electric
  • temperature touch pad
  • Cooling 1°C to 15°C
  • Heating 50°C to 65°C
  • Cooling to 30°C below ambient
  • 12/24 volt & mains leads included
  • 100% CFC free
Product Availability: Dometic Waeco Tropicool TCX14 Cool Box is sent via next working day carrier.

Product Name: Dometic Waeco Tropicool TCX21Thermoelectric AC/DC Cool Box
Product Description:
Dometic Waeco Tropicool TCX21 Thermoelectric 12/24v Cool Box

The middle capacity model of the popular trio of 'super' thermoelectric coolboxes from Dometic-WAECO.

The Dometic Waeco TCX21 Tropicool Portable Cooler enjoys the same temperature performance as the TCX14 and TCX35's, cooling right down to 30 deg C below the ambient temperature and heating to 65 deg C.

The Waeco Tropicool TCX21 Cool Box comes with both a 2 metre long UK/Eire 3 pin mains cable and a 2.8 metre long 12/24 volt DC power cable, with cigar lighter style plug. This can be plugged into any suitable powered vehicle socket with at least 4 amps for 12 volts or 3 amps for 24 volts of power available.

Suitable for a weekends camping, boating or caravan or motorhome use, the Waeco Tropicool TCX21 is also terrifically suitable as a Truck Coolbox with the 24 volt operation which is standard and can also keep pre-chilled items perfectly cool for the longest of journeys. Product Name: Dometic Waeco Tropicool TB08 12v Thermoelectric Cool Box
Product Description:
Dometic Waeco Tropicool TB08 Thermoelectric Car Cool Box

The Dometic Waeco Tropicool TB08 is an 8 litre thermoelectric cool box which is powered using a 12 volt cigarette lighter style socket as found in cars, caravans, motorhomes and boats.

Specially designed for rear car seats, the narrow shape of the Waeco TB08G Car Cooler means it fits nicely in the centre of the backseat, preventing it from taking up any unnecessary space. The TB08 Car Cool Box can be used as a dedicated beverage cooler in your vehicle and doubles up as a great armrest for your rear seat passengers.

The Waeco Tropicool TB08G Cool Box features a switch which reverses the polarity to take advantage of the coolbox's warming function, cools up to 20 °C below ambient temperature, and can heat to a maximum of 65°C whilst its carry handle and shoulder strap ensure easy transportation.

Dometic Waeco TB08 Car Cool Box Features:

  • LED indicators for cooling/heating function
  • Battery monitor
  • Safe fastening on the vehicle seat with the safety belt
  • Extensible fastening
  • Rail to avoid tilting in case of a sudden stop
  • Safe pressure closure,
  • ABS (Active Battery Security)
  • Can be switched to cold/warm
  • Fold-up grid tray
  • Serves as an armrest for extra comfort when fitted on the rear seat

Product Description:
Dometic Waeco Tropicool TB15 12v Car Cool Box

The Dometic Waeco Tropicool TB15G is a 15 litre luxury cool box which is specially designed and shaped to be placed in the centre of the back seat of a car, and as such can be used as a permanant beverage and snack cooler in your vehicle.

Use seat belts to secure the Waeco Tropicool TB15 Car Cooler into place and not only will items be protected from moving about whilst you're driving, but the innovative TB15 Cool Box can then also be doubled up for use as an armrest for two rear seat passengers.

The Waeco Tropicool TB15 Cool Box is powered using a 12 volt cigar lighter style socket while ignition is on and as well as being able to cool to 20 °C below ambient temperature can also heat to a maximum of 65°C (simply use the switch on the unit to reverse the polarity, thus producing warmth instead of cold!).

Product Description:
Dometic Waeco Cool Power EPS 100 Mains Adaptor

Specifically designed for connecting the Dometic Waeco COOLFREEZE CDF18 and CDF 25 to the mains, either at home or work or when hooked up on site.

Input Voltages 240 Volts mains and 12 or 24 volt DC. Output 25 Volts at 100 watts or 4 amps. The compressor cooling units are even more efficient on 24 volts and as a result the Dometic Waeco EPS 100 provides that voltage.

The 24 volts can not run back through the unit, so no damage can occur to 12 volt equipment that you have fitted in your vehicle! When permanently connected to mains this unit features mains priority, automatically switching to mains when it's detected and back to low voltage when hook up is lost or disconnected. 

Also suitable for for COOLMATIC, MDC, and CR compressor coolers, as well as the CB36 and 40, although the MPS-35 can be used as well.

Product Description:
Dometic NRX130C Caravan Fridge-Freezer

126L Compressor Cooled Refrigerator

The Dometic NRX130C Campervan Fridge-Freezer is a top of the line caravan kitchen appliance, perfect for your outdoor travels. This 126 litre compress-cooled refrigerator is designed to fit in motorhomes, campervans, and caravans. This compact freezer features a convenient full-width handle, reversible hinge and a removable 8.2 litre freezer. With a dark silver frameless door for a sleek aesthetic look, this energy efficient refrigerator brings a modern feel to your motor home. Perfect for outdoor leisure adventures, the removable freezer compartment can provide you with addition fridge space or an ideally sized freezer. A key feature of the NRX130 fridge is its three operating modes, include eco, boots and silent to suit your needs, use eco mode to save energy on the open road.

 

Stay fresh in winter mode with the smart closing mechanism which creates a gap between the fridge and door for airing out. The well equipped interior of the NRX130C Fridge suits your lifestyle with shelves, a bottle holder, door trays, crisper draws and a freezer. Everything you need!

 

NRX130C Fridge Key Features:

  • 3-in-1 cooling solution; fridge, freezer, or both at the same time
  • Sleek dark sliver frameless door
  • Premium compressor
  • Full width handle
  • Removable 8.2L freezer
  • Three cooling modes (Eco, Boost, Silent)
  • Energy efficient
  • Reversible door hinge for opening left or right
  • Dual function locks that can also act as vents for your fridge
  • Two crispers included for fruit and veg storage

Product Name: Dometic Waeco CRP40 Caravan Compressor Fridge
Product Description:
Discontinued

Dometic Waeco CoolMatic CRP40 Compressor Fridge

The Dometic Waeco CRP40 CoolMatic fridge is the only fridge freezer in the Waeco range that has a removable Danfoss compressor unit, which is mainly used for those who are really pushed for space. The compressor can either be attached the rear of the refrigerator - as shown in the picture - or placed to the side or above the unit to suit your needs (the compressor is attached with 1.5m flexible pipe). As it stands, the fridge will run off a 12 or 24 volt supply, but can also run on 230v mains when connected to a MPS35 mains adapter.

The unit has a 39 litre capacity including 5.3-litre freezer compartment situated at the top of the fridge. Like many compressor fridges, you can run the CRP40 off a single solar panel, which makes them ideal for camper vans and narrow boats where you may be without power for a few days.

  • Flush frame

Product Name: Hyundai HY32000SEi Leisure Inverter Petrol Generator
Product Description:
Hyundai HY32000SEi Leisure Generator

Full 3.2 Kw of portable mains power, with the convenience of Key Fob operated remote electric start. The HY32000SEi Leisure Generator can be key started electrically as well or has a hand operated starter cord. Powerful enough for large power tools, domestic kettles and even medium sized Air conditioner Units! 

The dual fuel version of the HY32000SEI, which was converted to run off LPG as well as petrol. This can be ideal for people with caravans or motorhomes, who keep a supply of LPG with them. This model features an electric key and remote starting function, which allows the generator to be started with a turn of a key, or remotely from a distance of 20 meters away.

The HY32000SEI uses pure sine wave technology, which allows for the safe usage of electronic equipment such as computers, lighting and phoen chargers. As well as using sine wave technology, this generator is powered by a 125cc HX125 four-stroke recoil start petrol engine.

Product Description:
N80 3-WAY STEPPED MOTORHOME and CARAVAN FRIDGE (DISCONTINUED) SEE N4080

The N80 is an absorption fridge from Thetford. With a capacity of 81 litres and includes a 10 litre freezer compartment, It is the most compact in the range, which makes it ideal for use in Caravans, Motorhomes and  larger Campervans etc, where space is limited, while still being practical for day to day use. It can be powered via 12 volt and mains, as well as having the ability to be run solely on LPG gas without needing to be connected to any electrical source.

Using Thetfords MEC (Manual Energy Control) system you can easily select how you would like it to be powered. Should you choose LPG gas you must press and hold the Piezo ignition button until the pilot light appears. The Thetford N80's door can be mounted on the left or the right to best suit your needs by just replacing a few screws.

Features

  • Stepped Wheelarch Model, Can be fitted over the wheelarch of the caravan or motorhome, or can allow ducts, pipes or wires to run below,
  • Piezo ignition No need for permanent 12 volt connection!
  • Securely closed door,
  • Flexible bottle slide,
  • 2 flexible door bins,
  • 2 flexible shelves,
  • Electronic Flame indicator,
  • Can be a stand alone Fridge working just from Lpg Gas in a remote location,
  • However it must still be built in to an externally vented, room sealed location,
  • Chimney connector supplied,
  • Vent Grills not supplied, see our 'related products,' page,

Benefits

  • First class cooling performance,
  • Absorption Technology, Quiet as a whisper!
  • 3-year guarantee,
  • CE marked, CFC-free and almost entirely recyclable

Thetford had some production/supply issues with fridge shelves towards the end of last year and rather than withhold entire production of the fridges, they issued a number of them without. You should find a note in the fridge explaining how to order them FOC directly to you.

Product Description:
This has been replaced by Thetford N4100 Motorhome Absorption Refrigerator

The Thetford N100 is a 3 way absorption fridge with electric ignition and is built for use in Leisure Vehicles e.g. Caravans, Motorhomes, Camper Vans and only with expert installation; Narrowboats.

With a total fridge capacity of 97 litres including a freezer compartment with a volume of 11 litres, the N100 is suitably sized for small to medium family sized RV's.

The top panel of the fridge features 3 main buttons; on/off button and 2 larger buttons which are used with the digital LCD display, one for mode selection and and the other for cooling level selection.

The N-100 can be run in 3 possible modes: 12 volt, mains and LPG gas and has a cooling range of -18°C below an ambient temperature of 25°C.

Features

  • Electronic ignition
  • Unique LCD display
  • Defrost cycle with self-diagnosis
  • Securely closed door
  • Flexible bottle slide
  • 2 flexible door bins
  • 2 flexible shelves
  • Flame indicator
  • Right Hand Hinging - Opens from the left

Benefits

  • First class cooling performance
  • Absorption Technology Quiet as a whisper
  • 3-year guarantee
  • CE mark of quality, CFC-free and almost entirely recyclable

Thetford had some production/supply issues with fridge shelves towards the end of last year and rather than withhold entire production of the fridges, they issued a number of them without. You should find a note in the fridge explaining how to order them FOC directly to you.

Product Name: Thetford N145 Caravan & Motorhome Fridge Freezer
Product Description:
Thetford N145 3 Way Fridge

Thetford N145 3 way absorption fridge is discontinued please see the N3145 for the replacement

The N145 is an all round 3 way fridge working on either 12 volt, gas or mains which makes it perfect for your caravan or motorhome. With Thetford’s SES (Smart Energy Selection) your N145 caravan fridge will never be disconnected on site when someone decides to unplug everything to mow the campsite lawn. With the SES choosing the best energy source, if it chooses gas it will be ignited electrically.

Some other great features of the N145 is it’s defrost cycle to prevent ice building up & the self diagnosis feature which brings up error codes on the LCD display to help sort out any internal problems.

Absolute quietness of the Thetford Norcold series is guaranteed despite how powerful it is, due to the cooling technlogy. The separate fridge/freezer compartments means when you open the one you want, you’re not letting all the cold air out of both of them so it keeps the fridge operating with more efficiency.

N145 Features

  • Total 141 Litres including a 23 Litre freezer
  • Seperate freezer door saves energy and keeps both compartments free from unneccessary warm air ingress!
  • Electric ignition
  • Unique LCD display
  • Defrost cycle and self-diagnostics
  • Securely closing door
  • Flexible bottle slide
  • 3 flexi fit shelves
  • 3 flexi fit door bins
  • Flame indicator
  • Right Hinged - Left Hand opening

N145 Benefits

  • First class cooling performance
  • Absorption Technology Quiet as a whisper
  • 3-year guarantee
  • CE mark of quality, CFC-free and almost entirely recyclable

Thetford had some production/supply issues with fridge shelves towards the end of last year and rather than withhold entire production of the fridges, they issued a number of them without. You should find a note in the fridge explaining how to order them FOC directly to you.

Product Name: Dometic RM122 2-Way Absorption Camper Van Fridge
Product Description:
Dometic RM122 2-Way Absorption Camper Van Fridge

The smallest Camper Van absorption fridge in our range of caravan refrigerators, the Dometic RM122 2-Way Absorption Camper Van Fridge is an ideal solution for those with limited space in their Camper Van kitchen or gallery with space efficient dimensions of just H58.5 x W38 x D44cm.

The Dometic RM122 2-Way Absorption Camper Van Fridge runs on 12v and LPG gas so that you can run on gas whilst you’re camping or just parked, and can then switch back to 12v when your Camper Van is back on the move again!

For a 3-way absorption fridge (which can run off 12v DC, 240v mains and LPG Gas) then check out the Dometic RM123 3-Way Absorption Fridge which provides the exact same features and dimensions but with additional mains operation.

The Dometic RM122 2-Way Absorption Fridge features include 

  • Absolutely silent absorption technology.
  • 30 Litre Capacity.
  • Must be vented top and bottom to work safely and economically, ventilation grills are available on our related products page.
  • Piezzo ignition and manual control means the RM122 can be run on just an Lpg supply, without any 12 volt connection if required. However it still has to be built in and properly vented.
  • All gas appliances must be fitted by a qualified gas engineer, failure to comply may affect your warranty.

Please note: Piezo ignition and features a modern light silver grey coloured cabinet and door. The door decor-panel can be easily changed.

Product Description:
Dometic RM123 230v 12v LPG Gas Caravan Fridge

The Vitrifrigo VTR5040 ES 3-way LPG gas 12v 24v compact caravan fridge is a potential replacement for the Dometic RM123 fridge.

The Dometic RM123 is our most compact '3-Way' Absorption Fridge available from Dometic.

Ideal for the smallest of camper vans, caravans or indeed any vehicle with minor refrigeration requirements! With the Dometic RM123 230v 12v LPG Gas Caravan Fridge requiring a space of just H58.5 x W38 x D44cm, this 3-way absorption fridge is terrifically space efficient, and with an adjustable thermostatic control whilst on gas or mains operations, the Dometic RM123 230v 12v LPG Gas Caravan Fridge is also incredibly easy to operate.

The Dometic RM123 230v 12v LPG Gas Caravan Fridge comes with a stylish design including a contemporary light silver grey coloured cabinet door, however, the front panel of the RM123 Caravan Fridge can also be easily changed for another design.

Dometic RM123 230v 12v LPG gas Caravan Fridge features include

  • Absolutely Silent Absorption Technology
  • Reigniter ignition system needs 12 volt permanent connection

Dometic 3 Way RMD 8555 Absorption Caravan Motorhome Fridge Refrigerator (Discontinued)

A Dometic large refrigerator, 2 door fridge freezer solution for caravans and motorhomes the Dometic RMD 8555 has identical size and consumption as the RMD8551 caravan motorhome refrigerator but with the added benefit of Automatic Energy Selection (AES).

  • AES version - Automatic Energy Selector
  • Replaceable door seals
  • Door locking with vent option
  • User-friendly integrated control panel
  • LED interior light and indicator lights visible from outside

Product Name: Dometic RM5310 230 v 12v LPG Gas Caravan Fridge
Product Description:
Dometic RM5310 230 v 12v LPG Gas Caravan Fridge - Discontinued

- Please see the VTR5060 as a suggested replacement

Featuring a contemporary, sophisticated design, freezer compartment (with 5 litre capacity) and a total capacity of 60 litres, the Dometic RM5310 3 Way Caravan Fridge is an easy to use, high quality 3 way absorption fridge with high performance cooling.

The Dometic RM5310 3 Way Caravan is a single door standard model in grey with battery ignition and features an illuminated interior in ice blue, easy to use control panel, integrated gas galvanometer (to monitor gas ignition being lit), and thermostat regulation in both 230v and gas mode.

To keep your goods tidy and organised within the Dometic RM5310 3 Way Caravan Fridge, the unit comes complete with an easily adjustable shelf system as well as sturdy door trays. For added security, particularly whilst your caravan or motorhome is in transit, the Dometic RM5310 also features a lockable door with magnetic seal and vent option.

Features of the Dometic RM5310 3 Way Caravan Fridge:

  • Colour: grey
  • LED interior light
  • User-friendly control panel
  • Flexible shelf system with practical door trays
  • Door with magnetic seal
  • Reversible door hinges
  • Battery-powered ignition unit
  • Thermostat regulation in 230-volt and gas mode
  • Door lock with vent option
  • Integrated gas galvanometer
  • All gas appliances must be fitted by a qualified gas engineer, failure to comply may affect your warranty.

Cooling capacity: refrigerator +7°C, freezer compartment down to –12°C at ambient temperatures up to 32°C (corresponds to climate class SN).

Product Name: Dometic RM5330 230v 12v LPG Gas Caravan Fridge
Product Description:
Dometic RM5330 230v 12v LPG Gas Caravan Fridge (Replaces Dometic RM4230)

The Dometic RM5330 is now discontinued. The closest alternative is the Vitrifrigo VTR5070 DG caravan fridge freezer.

The Dometic RM5330 is a wheel arch absorption fridge with a 70 Litre Capacity

Simple and straightforward to operate with its user friendly control panel and manual power source selection, the stepped Dometic RM5330 3-Way Absorption Caravan Fridge provides a high quality cooling performance alongside stylish and convenient features.

Boasting a separate 5 litre freezer compartment capable of freezing right down to -12° C, the Dometic RM5330 230v 12v LPG Gas Caravan Fridge also features an adjustable shelving system as well as a magnetic and manual mechanical safety lock / vent.

The Dometic RM5330 replaces the previous absorption fridge models; RM4230 and RM4233, and is exactly the same size.

With an internal LED light, changeable front panel as well as a galvanometer in the control panel allowing for easy monitoring of the LPG flame, the Dometic RM5330 230v 12v LPG Gas Caravan Fridge combines a stylish front with complete convenience.

The Dometic RM5330 Caravan 3 Way Absorption Fridge features include

  • Absorption technology is Absolutely Silent!
  • Ignition for lpg operation is provided by its own dry cell battery
  • 70 Litres Total space, including a 5 Litre Freezer Compartment, 
  • Can be installed where there is no mains or 12v power supply,
  • The unit must however still be properly fitted into a room sealed, and outside ventilated unit,
  • A further rotary control sets the required temperature, which is maintained automatically by thermostatic control on mains and lpg gas
  • The RM5330 comes complete with a 'chimney-kit' for the venting of heat and gases from the boiling tube,
  • The top and bottom ventilation grill are extra and available on our related product pages
  • All gas appliances must be fitted by a qualified gas engineer, failure to comply may affect your warranty.

 

*Wheelarch models have a section at the bottom rear of the cabinet cut away. This was traditionally used when the fridge was placed directly over the Caravan or Motorhome wheel and can also be utilised to clear warm/cold blown air trunking or even electrical cabling or water pipes.

Product Name: Dometic Smev 9222 Sink and Hob Combination Unit Inc Template
Product Description:
Smev 9222 (Now Dometic HSG 2370) 2 Burner Hob & Sink Combination - Including Template

Compact LPG Cooker for Campervans, Caravans & Motorhomes with Piezo Ignition – Left or Right Hand

Upgrade your camper kitchen with the Smev 9222, now known as the Dometic HSG 2370. This premium 2-burner hob and sink combination is designed for campervans, caravans, and motorhomes, providing efficient cooking and washing in one compact, durable unit. Built for off-grid adventures, the 9222 offers style, safety, and functionality in limited space.

The Smev 9222 is engineered with compact design and durability in mind, making it ideal for camper conversions and tight motorhome kitchen layouts. Its twin heat-resistant glass lids fold down to create additional worktop space, helping you maximize every inch of your living area. This space-saving feature is perfect for van conversions, caravans, and off-grid setups, where versatility and efficiency are essential. The high-quality materials and robust construction of the Smev 9222 ensure reliable performance and long-lasting durability.

Features & Benefits

  • 2-Burner LPG Hob & Sink Combo: Efficient, space-saving design for compact kitchens.
  • High-Quality Construction: Made from premium materials for long-lasting use.
  • Twin Heat-Resistant Glass Lids: Close for extra workspace when not in use.
  • Piezo Ignition System: Convenient push-button ignition; no 12V supply needed.
  • Flame Failure Safety Device: Automatically shuts off gas if the flame goes out.
  • Left or Right-Hand Option: Choose the version that suits your layout (sink left or right).
  • Detachable Pan Supports: Easy to remove and clean.
  • 39mm Tap Hole: Fits most folding caravan taps (tap sold separately).
  • Seal, Siphon & Template Included: Everything needed for installation.
  • Gas Consumption: 204 g/h
  • Fomerly known as Smev 9222

Left or Right?

  • When facing the 9222: if the sink is on the right, it’s a right-hand model; if the sink is on the left, choose the left-hand version.

Installation & Compatibility

Ideal for campervans, motorhomes, caravans, and off-grid conversions. Operates on LPG gas. The installation template is printed on the box for easy fitting.

Please note: The Dometic warranty does not cover the Smev 9222/HSG 2370 for boat or marine use, including inland and offshore waterways.

Product Name: Dometic RM8501 3 Way Absorption Caravan Fridge
Product Description:
Dometic RM8501 Caravan and Motorhome Fridge

Featuring a 106 Litre total capacity and removable freezer compartment, the Dometic RM8501 Caravan and Motorhome Fridge is a secure, high quality and durable 3 way absorption refrigerator specifically designed for use in campervans, motorhomes and caravans.

The Dometic RM8501 Caravan and Motorhome Fridge is provided with a new control panel enhanced with an integrated LED display and control system (replete with handy visual alarm signals) for simple monitoring and management as well as a manual energy selection (MES) system.

For secure storage and easy access to your goods, the Dometic RM8501 Caravan and Motorhome Fridge features an innovative locking system with fingertip-opening as well as an adjustable and ergonomic shelving system with spill protection for you to efficiently and securely store your goods.

Dometic RM8501 Caravan and Motorhome Fridge Features:

  • 106 Litre Gross Capacity
  • 9 Litre Capacity Freezer Compartment
  • Magnetic door seal
  • Removable freezer compartment
  • Door locking with vent option
  • Interior light
  • Thermostat control for 230v & gas operation
  • MES manual energy selection (with touch control panel)
  • Electronic gas ignition
  • Low gas consumption (no standby mode)
  • 12v Supply is required for control unit for unit to operate.
  • Electronic re-ignition if the flame goes out
  • 3 stage manual gas control
  • Replaceable door seal
  • Please ensure you have measured the fridge correctly before purchasing, re-stock fees can apply if a fridge has been opened.
  • All gas appliances must be fitted by a qualified gas engineer, failure to comply may affect your warranty.

Please note: The Dometic RM8501 Caravan Fridge is available as either a right handed or left handed model (whilst looking at the fridge, right handed indicates that the hinge is on the right, left handed indicates that the hinge is on the left).

Product Name: Propex Heatsource HS2000 12v LPG Gas Blown Air Heater
Product Description:
Propex HS2000 Heater

Suitable for use on a variety of vehicles including caravans, boats, horseboxes and motorhomes, the Propex HS2000 Heater is a heat source that functions completely independent of the engine.

Fueled by either propane or butane, this Propex Heater is an automatic blown air heating system that is a clean and efficient method for heating your campervan, caravan or RV. The HS2000 uses a dependable thermostat to measure room temperature and automatically ignites and heats the room should it drop below the selected temperature (switching off when the optimal temperature is achieved).

The Propex HS2000 Heater is available for purchase as a single, double or triple kit - please indicate your preferences for both in the appropriate drop down menus / boxes above, before checkout.

What do you get in the different kits?

A single outlet vehicle kit (V1) contains:

  • 1 x 1 metre 60mm ducting
  • 1 x 1 metre combustion inlet pipe
  • 1 x 0.75 meter Stainless Steel Exhaust pipe
  • 1 x Thermostat
  • 3.5 metres thermostat wiring harness
  • 3.5 metres 12v supply harness
  • 1 directional hot air outlet
  • 1 directional cool air return vent
  • hose clips, fasteners, screws, inline fuse, instructions, drilling template

A twin outlet vehicle fitting kit (V2) contains:

  • As a V1 kit with the addition of
  • 1 x open/close vent
  • 1 x Y branch
  • Extra metre of 60mm hot air ducting
  • Extra hose clips, fasteners and screws

A three outlet vehicle fitting kit (V3) contains:

  • As V1 + V2
  • An additional Y branch
  • An additional open/close vent
  • An extra metre of 60mm ducting – so 3 metres in total
  • Extra hose clips, fasteners and screws as required.

Gas Consumption Figures

  • Gas Consumption figures (under continuous operation):
  • Average consumption 142 grams/hour
  • 3.9kg propane cylinder will last - 27.5 hours
  • 4.5kg butane 31.7 hours
  • 13kg propane 91.5 hours
  • 15kg butane 105.6 hours
  • 19kg butane 133.8 hours

Product Name: Propex 10L Mains Powered Water Storage Heater
Product Description:
Propex 10L Mains Powered Water Storage Heater

Designed specifically for use in caravans and motorhomes, the Propex 10L Mains Powered Water Storage Heater is an adjustable water heater featuring an appealing, modern design. Providing choices to ensure that your needs are met, the Propex 10L Water Heater comes with a variety of mounting options and variable temperature settings and is built from high grade, durable materials for a long lasting finish.

This item is now discontinued please see the replacement Propex 10L Electric Water Storage Heater!

The compact design of the Propex 10L Water Heater makes it incredibly easy for mounting in a variety of spaces including a bedbox, locker or under seat area whilst multiple integrated protection devices guard against over pressure, electricity leakage and over temperature.

Longevity is also assured with a build composed of corrosion and water scale resistant materials (an inner tank made of super steel plate with enamel coating) whilst the ultra thick, non-CFC Polyurethane Foam is integral for preventing heat loss and reducing energy costs.

The 10L Mains Powered Water Storage Heater by Propex also comes complete with a temperature meter, adjustment knob, choice of pipe connections and comes fitted with a 3 pin plus for a quick and easy installation.

Product Name: Propex Malaga 5E Electric LPG Gas Water Storage Heater (Updated 4E)
Product Description:
Propex Malaga 5E Water Heater

Gas and Electric Water Heater

A high capacity water storage heater, the Propex Malaga 5 Water Heater is available either as a powerful, standard gas heater or is included with the added advantage of a 750 watt electric heating element (The Malaga E). Whichever version of the Propex Malaga 5 Water Heater you decide upon, you're guaranteed a product with a fast and efficient supply of hot water (so showering in tour vans or caravans will be a breeze).

This Propex Water Heater is also suitable for installation in boats used exclusively on Inland Waterways (i.e Class 1 and 2) so long as they're mounted in a suitable position. As the Malaga 5 Water Heater is also a room sealed appliance, it conforms to Boat Safety Requirements.

A Water Heater with Micro-Processor Controller Electronics

For accurate digital control of the safety functions and heater operations, the Malaga 5 Water Heater is equipped with the latest Propex electronics to provide you with complete ease of management. With a switch panel that features a 3 position switch with which to select power options (i.e gas only, gas and 230v etc.) and an LED that can indicate when the gas burner is operating as well as highlighting fault conditions, the Propex Malaga 5 Water Heater provides optimal usability and control.

Propex Malaga 5E Electric LPG Gas Water Storage Heater features:

  • Large capacity (13L) for longer showering and washing facilities
  • Efficient gas burner for a faster warm up
  • Heat up time from 15 to 70°C: 28 mins using gas + electric, 43 mins using gas only, and 64 mins using electric only
  • 750W element (on Malaga E) can be used alone or with gas burner for quicker hot water
  • Small flue terminal for outwardly neat appearance
  • Reassuringly safe to use (combustion products completely sealed from caravan interior)
  • All controls accessible at the rear of the unit for easy installation and maintenance
  • Electronic control for quick and easy burner supervision and usage
  • Automatic overheat cut out (with reset capability)
  • Compact size providing more space to route pipe work and ducting where needed
  • 12mm Water Connections
  • 8mm Gas Connections

Water Supply & Installation Requirements:

  • The heater will operate satisfactorily on either a system where the pump is controlled by the tap micro switches or one controlled by a pressure switch.
  • It must not be connected to a mains water supply.
  • Water connections can be provided to suit a range of standard fittings.
  • Reinforced or semi rigid pipe must be used.
  • Heater should be floor mounted (or suitably supported) as normal in the bed box
  • Flue terminal position shouldn’t be closer than 300mm below an opening window or 600mm from a vertical corner
  • Clearances required for installation and servicing are as seen from inside the caravan
  • Maximum water pressure 28 PSI (2 Bar) This is not suitable for 30 PSI pumps. 

Adapter Plate - please note the adapter plate is only required when changing from a Carver boiler. If you are installing the unit as new, you will not require it. If you are unsure, please call our technical advice line on 0151 334 0222 and select option 2.

Truma Combi D6 / D6E Diesel Caravan Air and Water Heater
Product Description:
Truma Combi D6 Diesel Air Space and Water Heater for Caravan Motorhome Campervan


An efficient heating solution for your motorhome, campervan or caravan, the Truma Combi D6 Diesel Heater has all the benefits of a Truma Combi Heater with a diesel burner instead of gas, and combines hot air and water heating into the one easy to use and convenient unit.

Lightweight and compact

Despite the ability to operate as both a space heater and hot water boiler, the Combi D6 is extremely small and lightweight. Featuring a 10 litre water tank, it can provide enough water for day-to-day tasks such as washing hands and dishes and even a quick shower as well as heating your living space.

Flexibility to suit your needs

With optimum air distribution through four warm air outlets and easy temperature adjustment via the digital control panel, the Combi D6 also allows you complete control over function at any moment, giving you easily changeable options between hot air, hot water or even having both at once.

Optional 230V mains electric available

The Combi D6 is also available with a mains electric heater element alongside the diesel heater as the D6E model. This not only allows you to heat water and living space air using diesel, but alternatively you can use the electric element when diesel isn't available, and you can even use both diesel and electric together.

The Combi D6 / D6E kit contains:

  • Truma Combi D6 diesel unit or optional Combi D6E diesel and electric unit.
  • Truma CP Plus digital control panel

New installations will require are a Truma cowling kit, an exhaust pipe, and a cowl panel as detailed below. Please note that the Truma Room Temperature Sensor Cable is not included in the kit.

Includes digital control panel -iNet ready

The Truma Combi D6E complete kit includes a digital control panel which is iNet ready*. The Truma iNet system allows convenient control of your Combi D6 from your mobile phone or tablet via an app. Additionally, if you have a Truma air-conditioning unit installed, the control panel can automatically co-ordinate the heater and air conditioning unit to ensure your living space maintains a comfortable and controlled environment.

* To use the Truma iNet system with your Combi 6 / 6E you will need a Truma iNet controller available here.

Additional extra's for new Combi D6 / D6E installations

Please note that ducting, exhaust pipes, and wall cowl vents are NOT included with the Truma Combi D6. For a new installation you will require appropriate ducting, exhaust pipes, and wall cowl vents.

Product Name: Vision Plus Status 350 Digital Caravan TV Aerial
Product Description:
Vision Plus Status 350 Caravan TV Aerial 

Please note! Now comes with the Status VP3 Matched Amplifier, as in the above pictures.

The Vision Plus Status 350 Caravan TV Aerial is the updated version of the 315/335/355; it looks and fits the same as the 315/335/355, but benefits from improved performance, and is the most successful omni-directional TV antenna in the UK with a proven track record.

Depending on your particular installation, the Vision Plus Status 350 Aerial is available with two different cable lengths the 350/1, which has 1 metre of coaxial cable, and the 350/10 with of course 10 metres of cable, please indicate your preference from the drop down menu at the top of the page prior to checkout, with both designed to accommodate for complete versatility with three fitting options offered as standard: Permanent Fitting, 25mm Mast Fitting and an optional Suction Pad Fitting Kit.

The Central Pinnacle of the Vision Plus Status 350 Caravan TV Aerial can be easily unscrewed for instances where storage height is a problem, and the antenna can even be removed, leaving the mounting foot in place, which can be sealed with a blanking cap. Straight forward and user friendly, once you’ve fitted the aerial, all you need to do is switch your television on and tune in.

The Vision Plus Status 350 Aerial: Transmission and Reception:

In a number of countries overseas as well as the UK, TV signals are transmitted horizontally and vertically, with vertical receptions requiring a vertical receiver. The Vision Plus Status 350 Aerial accomplishes this with its Central Pinnacle; a smart solution which gives the aerial it’s idiosyncratic, charming profile.

As a result the Vision Plus Status 350 Aerial can be finely adjusted to remain level on roof gradients of up to 22 degrees – a unique feature only offered by Vision Plus Status Aerials.

Please note:

  • TV reception can be greatly affected by the orientation of the antenna, and as such it’s crucial that all antennas are mounted level!
  • Supplied with The Vision Plus VP3 Digital Amplifier. Used for boosting the performance of all non amplified directional portable TV aerials. This also has a non-amplified outlet for FM Radio reception when used in conjunction with a UHF/FM antenna. The powerful little Vision Plus VP3 amplifier will provide great results and performance especially in areas where reception is poor, allowing you to enjoy your caravan or motorhome break with clear tv reception.

Vision Plus VP2 TV antenna signal booster

The Vision Plus VP2 Digital Aerial Signal Amplifier is a fully wideband booster for television transmissions and is designed to be used with Vision Plus Status antennas with orange logos and don't have the pullout telescopics.

Product Name: Dometic Freshjet 1100 Campervan Motorhome Air Conditioner
Product Description:
The Dometic Freshjet 1100 Roof Air Conditioner For Small Caravans Campervans and Motorhomes

The Freshjet 1100 is the smallest Dometic roof air conditioner on the market, it’s light and compact leaving plenty of room for other roof accessories in your campervan or caravan. Even though it’s designed for small recreational vehicles (Up to 5m), owners of a motorhome larger than 5 metres in length could have 2 Freshjet 1100 fitted to create 2 different climates.

Other useful features of the Freshjet 1100 Air Conditioner:

  • Big 1000 Watts of cool conditioning ( 3400 Btu ) No Heating Facility on this unit
  • Circuit protection for campsites: 3 A delay fuse. Only a 3 amp campsite hook up required
  • All main functions of the Freshjet 1100 can be controlled by remote control
  • Integrated LED lights
  • The Freshjet 1000 air conditioning is distributed by four adjustable air vents
  • The 1100 is only for stationary use unless used with DC Kit 1 or DC Kit 3
  • The Dometic Freshjet 1100 requires a 400mm x 400mm cut out or replaces a 'standard' 400mm x 400mm roof light like a Seitz Mini Heki

What do I get?

Everything you need to install a compact Airconditioner to your sub 5 metre leisure vehicle whilst connected to 230 volts hook up, complete with remote control.

What else do I need?

A suitable mains power supply to the roof of the vehicle. A Dometic DC Kit 1, if you wish to run the Freshwell 1100 airconditioning unit whilst driving, Please note the DC Kits include a full wiring kit. Please see our items to the right of this page, oh and you'll also need a tube of sealant!

Dometic Freshjet 1100 Air Conditioner:

 

This product must be installed by a Dometic approved installer, to not do so will affect the warranty on the product.

Installation Manuals

Operating System

 

Please Note: If you will be traveling to warmer Climates i.e. South of France, Spain, Italy etc. You will need to oversize your air con otherwise the Air con will struggle to cool your vehicle!

Product Description:
The Dometic B1600 Plus Air Conditioner quiet with improved efficiency

The Dometic Blizzard B1600 Plus Caravan or Motorhome air conditioner is designed to be fitted to Motorhomes and caravans up to six metres in length. The B1600 Plus Air Conditioner has the same aerodynamic design, easy installation and quiet operation as its predecessor the B1500 but now has an improved air allocation system, this means the B1600 is more efficient in the way it distributes cool air from it's rotary compressor.

2 Fan speeds front or rear air conditioning or heating

Practical ideas built into the B1600 Plus Air Conditioner are such things as being able to choose between front or rear distribution or both at once with a 2 speed fan, and B1600 Plus also has the ability to heat as standard.

Other features of the Dometic B1600 Plus Air Conditioner:

  • Includes easy to use remote control! Ideal if your roof is very high, or for the luxury of adjusting conditioning from the comfort of your seat or bed.
  • This air conditioning unit as delivered is designed for stationary mains 240 volt use. If it’s used in combination with DC Kit 2 or DC Kit 3 then you can easily have conditioning whilst on your journey
  • Fitted control panel, with led indicators and flap control featuring integrated lighting
  • Suitable for most UK and European campsites  (With at least 4 Amp hook up post)

What do I get?

Everything you need to run a powerful 1500 watts of chilled air conditioning or 800 watts of heating, comes with the controllable air distribution panel and full remote control.

What do I need?

To run on 240 volts mains, just a tube of sealant and mains supply cable! To run whilst 'on the move' a Dometic DC Kit 2 or Dometic DC Kit 3, both of which inlude a full wiring kit, see our extras on the right.

Product Name: Dometic B2200 Caravan & Motorhome Air Conditioner
Product Description:
The Dometic B2200 Air Con is high powered with low noise and vibration levels

The Dometic B2200 caravan and motorhome air conditioner is the elegant and higher powered version of the B1600 Plus, and yet identical in physical size, and just 4 kilos more in weight, Exceptionally high performance combined with low vibration and noise levels. The Dometic B2200 Air Conditioner is suitable for a caravan or motorhome up to 7 metres internal length. Its air diffusion box can distribute cool air front and back or just to the front or back, or warm air to either both sides or just one, You are able to control fan speeds independently.

Easy to install

The Dometic B2200 caravan and motorhome air conditioner is easy to install and can adjust to the roof thickness. The Dometic B2200 has safe operation, tilt insensitive up to 10 degrees, integrated control panel and illuminations.

The B2200 caravan and motorhome air conditioner also features:

  • High performance heating function; 1200 watts.
  • Designed for stationary operation as delivered on mains 240v , if used in combination with DC Kit 2 or DC Kit 3 then mobile operation is possible.
  • Circuit protection for campsites: 5 A delay fuse. Power post requirement > 6amps.
  • Full function Remote Control

What do I get?

The unit is delivered fully equipped and ready for 240 volt installation, the full function remote and air distribution panel are all in the box.

What else do I need?

For 240 volt use just a tube of sealant and the 240 volt supply cables to the unit. For on-the-road 'chilling and heating' a Dometic DC Kit 2 or Dometic DC Kit 3, Please note the DC kits include all of the neccesary wiring. Please see our additional items panel to the right.

Product Description:
The Dometic B2600 Air Conditioner provides powerful heating and cooling

The Dometic B2600 conditioning has very high technical specifications. This is one of the Dometic caravan and motorhome roof mounted units.  One of the Dometic 'Comfort Class' Air conditioning units and one of very few models in the industry to feature an integrated energy efficient heat pump technology system. The B2600 supplies powerful heating; 3300 watts and cool air conditioning; 2500 watts. Like all the other mid range Dometic Air conditioners it can variably direct the flow direction as well as control the amount of air for your comfort, with it's built in 4 speed blower.

Other features of the Dometic B2600 air conditioner:

  • User friendly full featured remote control bringing an added luxury to your caravan or motorhome
  • Comes with mounting frame and fixing materials
  • Air vent control panel with integrated lighting and status led's
  • As delivered suitable for 230-volt AC stationary operation unless used with the optional DC Kit 4 which provides fully mobile operation
  • 6A delay fuse, means a hook up post of at least 6 amps needs to be available for campsite operation
  • Up to 8 metre internal caravan or motorhome length suitability.

What do get with the unit?

The unit complete with interior air distribution panel, remote control, and full instructions. All ready for 230 volt operation, after connection to a suitable mains supply led to the vehicles roof.

What else may I need?

Simply, a tube of sealant and either a 40cm x 40cm existing rooflight cut out or new cut out! For use on the move the Dometic DC Kit 4 is also required. Please see our optional extras link on the right.

Product Description:
The Dometic B3200 Air Conditioner for a large caravan or motorhome;

The Dometic B3200 is the new and updated version of the B3000, both of which are designed for the larger motorhomes or caravans, that is provided the roof is strong enough for its 45kg weight! ( Please check with your dealer or manufacturer.) The B3200 Air conditioner is the highest powered of the Dometic range currently available. Rugged and reliable even in the very worst or hottest of weather conditions.

It’s a professional class Air Conditiong Unit also suitable for Commercial Vehicles

Even with its large size and power it saves on your interior space whilst still being able to deliver the treated air very efficiently, with so many  different air outlet positions front, back and sideways, all delivered by a three speed blower. This professional class roof air conditioner is built to keep you in a comfortable climate whether it’s boiling hot or freezing cold and will also do it quietly!

Other features of the B3200 Air Conditioner:

  • The B3200 is tilt insensitive up to 8 degrees from horizontal,
  • Integral control panel
  • Circuit protection for campsites: 7A delay fuse, Please note; a 10 amp hook up power post supply is required on caravan sites
  • The B3200 is designed for stationary operation but mobile use is also possible with the Dometic (DC Kit 4)
  • Please note the opening required for the Dometic B3200 in the roof is just 362mm x 362mm, rather than the usual 400mm x 400mm

What do I get?

The unit itself, supplying a full 3200 watts of air cooling power and 1600 watts of air heating power, and the interior distribution panel in an additional carton. The panel distributes cool air through an impressive 5 outlets and warm through 2. The controls are conveniently mounted on the distribution panel. (Remote is not available on this model.) Ready to go on 240 volt power.

What else do I need?

Just a suitable mains cable to the airconditioner's roof location, ( *A full wiring kit is included in optional Dometic DC Kit 4. ) And you'll need a tube of sealant! The DC Kit 4, featured on the right is required to operate the airconditioning unit whilst you are 'on-the-move.'

Product Name: Dometic HB2500 Under Bench Air Conditioner
Product Description:
The HB2500 Our Biggest Selling and Most Popular Dometic Air Conditioner

Please note: This product has been discontinued and replaced by the Dometic Freshwell 3000.

Its an under bed or bench Air Conditioner and heater:

The Dometic HB2500 is the first Caravan and Motorhome air conditioner designed to be built into a bench or bed locker. It also has a powerful heating element for effective heating of your caravan or motorhome.

Its hidden away and it purifies the air:

The Dometic HB2500 Air Conditioner also purifies the air before it distributes it through the caravan via a choice of 3 side or end outlets, which can be uniquely modified to your caravan or motorhome. The benefits of an under bench air conditioner can't be understated, no extra roof load or space taken up, the outer dimensions, drag and physical properties of the caravan or motorhome remain the same.

The Dometic HB2500 Caravan Motorhome Air Conditioner includes these features:

  • Low noise and weight,
  • The HB2500 has night time silent control and timer programming which can be comfortably set by remote control.
  • Designed for stationary operation (230 volts), but in combination with DC-Kit 3 also for mobile use
  • Circuit protection for campsites: 6 A delay fuse.
  • Blower speeds x 3

What do I get?

The HB2500 is ready for mains installation, complete with a hold down kit and remote control sensor and remote control. The Dometic HB2500 features a triple air outlet on one corner of the unit, this has a blanking plug included. Using the blanking plug you can select airflow from either the rear or side of the HB2500 or even use all six outlets! Distribution is normally by flexible ducting, see our accessory range. 

The ducting delivers the chilled air to the roof level for optimum performance. The Dometic HB2500 is possibly one of the easiest methods of installing air conditioning around today!

What else do I need? (see ducting and vents in the right hand column of this page)

Product Description:
The Dometic Freshlight 1600 Air Conditioner with roof light (DISCONTINUED)

For alternatives please see the Dometic Freshlight 2200 or Dometic Freshjet 1700

Need an air conditioner a roof light (natural daylight) but don’t have space? Then the Dometic Freshlight 1600 is for you!

Air Conditioning with a natural daylight roof light

Developed in conjunction with Seitz (roof light manufacturers), The Freshlight 1600 incorporates a fixed roof window and air conditioner giving a gentle light for an evening ambience, it also has a single pleated blind for night time. The Freshlight 1600 incorporates an active vent system that keeps your motorhome or caravan supplied with fresh air quickly.   

Ideal for retaining light from an existing 40cm x 40cm or Midi-Heki 70cm x 50cm Roof light, you can even replace the Air Conditioner with the Midi Heki when you sell the vehicle, and fit it to your new caravan or motorhome.


Other features of the Dometic Freshlight 1600:

The complete external air conditioning unit, the interior air distribution panel, the unit is complete with remote control, blackout blind and led lights.

What else do I need?

A strong non-setting sealant like Sikaflex 221 to create a flexible watertight seal around the exterior of the Dometic Freshlight Air conditioner.

Product Name: Dometic Freshlight 2200 Caravan Motorhome Air Conditioner
Product Description:
The Dometic Freshlight 2200 giving your motorhome a comfortable climate and an inclusive roof window/light

The Dometic Freshlight 2200 Motorhome Air Conditioner is the more powerful version of the Freshlight 1600 Conditioner, with a huge 2200 watts/7500 Btu of Cooling Power! The Dometic Freshlight is suitable for any Motorhome or caravan up to 7 metres in length.

Cools, heats and provides de-humidified and filtered air

This Air Conditioner delivers cool, de-humidified air and filters away dust and dirt particles. You can set the temperature you want to cool or heat the air as required. The Dometic Freshlight 2200 air conditioner can be powered via a mains hook-up, a leisure generator or inverter.

It's a light, flexible and efficient conditioning system for your motorhome or caravan

The Freshlight 2200 Air Conditioner concept was developed in conjunction with Dometic-Seitz, the Dometic window and roof light manufacturer, which means natural light can be retained from an existing 40 cm x 40 cm or Heki Midi 70 cm x 50 cm roof light.

No need to let the Freshlight 2200 air conditioner go when you sell your caravan or motorhome, just swap it for a roof window

Another benefit is that the Freshlight 2200 Air Conditioner is that it can be taken out when you sell your motorhome or caravan and simply replaced with a Heki-Midi roof window. The Freshlight 2200 Conditioning unit comes with natural ventilation, subtle ambient lighting as well as a blackout blind for a relaxed night's sleep. Product Description:
Vitrifrigo C90i 12/24v Compressor Motorhome Fridge

The Vitrifrigo C90 is a 90-liter 12V/24V compressor fridge that is designed for use in motorhomes, campervans, caravans and marine application. The fridge has a unique Airlock catch that provides a positive lock and a vent position for air circulation. It also has an internal LED light and a 9.1-liter ice box.

The C90 is a very power-efficient fridge, using the BD35 compressor and aluminium-finned condenser. This makes it ideal for anyone looking to get the most out of their 12V/24V system and solar setup while staying off-grid, and for those looking to make the most of their space in a campervan, caravan, or motorhome.

Vitrifrigo C90i Compressor Fridge Key Features:

  • Internal light as standard
  • Temperature controlled by a mechanical thermostat.
  • 9.8 litre ice box

Product Name: Thetford Spinflo Triplex Caravan Cooker 3 Burner Hob Oven And Grill With Lid Gas Shut Off
Product Description:
Thetford Spinflo Triplex Caravan LPG Cooker (Hob, Oven & Grill)

The Triplex caravan and motorhome cooker consists of a 3 burner hob, 36 litre combined oven and grill, making it an ideal solution for most applications. The cooker features: 12v electronic ignition, flame failure devices on all 3 burners and a stainless steel interior. This unit offers an extremely attractive yet compact cooking solution in even the smallest galley.

The Triplex oven is designed for 'built-in' installation. The unit is effectively supported by the worktop to the sides and rear of the unit, screw holes are provided to screw outwards into the worktops and additionally the oven can be also be screwed to the galley to each side if required. The oven should vent into its own sealed space to the rear of the unit, ventilated at floor level with a drop vent to the outside of the vehicle.

  • Please ensure you have measured the oven correctly before purchasing, re-stock fees can apply if an oven has been opened.
  • Please note - Thetford are transitioning to clear glass across their cooker range. Your oven glass may have clear glass instead of smoked

 

Features:

  • Lid glass with or without shut off
  • Lightweight
  • High-quality materials and components
  • Stainless interior
  • Easy to clean
  • Grill pan kit
  • 2 oven shelves
  • Chrome pan support

Technical Details:

  • Total heat input (gas): 9.2 kW
  • Knobs: matt nickel straight
  • Min 29cm clearance needed for oven door (body of oven to end of door when open)

All gas appliances must be fitted by a qualified gas engineer, failure to comply will affect your warranty.

Product Name: Dometic Freshjet FJX4 1700 Caravan Motorhome Air Conditioner
Product Description:
Dometic Freshjet FJX4 1700 Caravan Motorhome Air Conditioner

The Dometic FreshJet FJX4 1700 roof mounted Air Conditioner is the new generation air con designed to keep your caravan, campervan, or motorhome cool and comfortable. It boasts a powerful 1700 watts of cooling capacity, making it ideal for motorhomes up to 6 meters in length. This Dometic air conditioner has really quiet operation, keeping your caravan or motorhome cool without unwanted noise. It also features the CleanAir system, which actively reduces allergens, bacteria, and mold to ensure fresh, clean air inside your motorhome, camper or caravan.

For added convenience, the Dometic FreshJet FJX4 1700 air con offers smart connectivity feature for you mobile phone. You can control the temperature and settings with a remote control (included), smartphone app or directly through the control panel. The Dometic FJX4 1700 air conditioner provides both cooling and heating functionality, ensuring year-round comfort.

The new air distribution box that comes with this unit is lightweight and compact, making it particularly suitable for caravans where weight is a concern. The design also optimizes airflow for quiet and efficient cooling in two directions. The user-friendly interface features a flush-mounted touch control display that allows you to easily set the desired temperature and fan speed.
Finally, the Dometic FreshJet FJX4 1700 boasts a stylish design that integrates seamlessly with modern Motorhome interiors. The elegant unit even features built-in LED lights that cast a warm and soft ambient glow into your caravan.

Features of the Freshjet FJX4 1700 Air Con:

  • Key Features of the Dometic Freshjet fjx4 1700:
  • Ideal for vehicles up to 6 m in length
  • Cooling capacity: 1700 watts
  • Heating capacity: 800 watts
  • Cooling and Heating Function
  • Modern design - aerodynamically shaped rooftop air con
  • Air distribution box with touch control panel and integrated ambient light
  • Optimised Airflow - low-profile air distribution box with powerful front and back airflow
  • Superior cooling performance – the cabin is cooled down quicker than previous Freshjet 1700
  • Quieter than other roof air conditioners available in the market
  • Superior energy efficiency – reduced power consumption
  • CleanAir air purifier system – keeps your motorhome smelling fresh and clean
  • Remote control included as standard
  • Smart connectivity options – compatible with Dometic smart phone climate app
  • The FreshJet can easily be retro fitted in replacement of your existing 400 x 400 roof vent (subject to the roof vent location, & roof space for the AC unit), alternatively it can be retro fitted with 400 x 400 roof cut out.
  • Ideal for recreational vehicles, the unit can also be operated efficiently on the move with the option of a DC Kit - DSP-T 12 (12V)

Product Name: Dometic Freshjet FJX7 2200 Motorhome Inverter Air Conditioner
Product Description:
Dometic FreshJet FJX7 2200 Motorhome Caravan Inverter Air Conditioner

Modern and Reliable Air Conditioning with a Sleek Design

Stay cool on your next camping adventure with the Dometic Freshjet FJX7 2200 Air Conditioner, a new generation 2200 W air conditioner with an electronic inverter compressor that produces the same performance as the Dometic Blizzard 2200. The Air Conditioner comes fitted with the latest speed-controlled inverter compressor and heat pump technology. This will allow you to quickly, quietly and efficiently cool or heat your caravan, motorhome or campervan! The Air Conditioner is a roof unit and needs to be fitted to the rooftop. The design is sleek, elegant and minimalistic with an LED light curve to complement your caravan / motorhome's aesthetics and provide an element of ambiance at night.

21st Century Motorhome Air Conditioning

The Dometic Freshjet FJX7 2200 Rooftop Air Conditioner is equipped with Smart connectivity features, which will allow users to control the heating through a range of convenient touchpoints, such as the smart phone app, a remote control or the built-in touch screen interface. Perfect to help modify any campervan into a mobile smart home! The integrated CleanAir system helps to maintain Air Quality within a Caravan or Motorhome by keeping the air fresh and clear, and working to remove allergens, bacteria and mould. The Air Conditioner unit is equipped with Smart Technology, where users can set the device to the automatic setting and allow the device to adjust to the temperature and air quality independently throughout the day. The smart-phone app, remote control and touchscreen provide a variety of options for manual adjustments to the temperature.

Compact and Discreet Caravan Air Conditioning

The Dometic Freshjext FJX7 2200 Roof Air Conditioner is one of the most lightweight and ultra-compact motorhome / caravan air conditioners in all of Europe. It is ideal for motorhomes or caravans up to 7m in length, and all campervans models because of it's small design and powerful features. The sleep mode feature reduces fan speed by 80%, creating a peaceful, temperature-controlled environment to enjoy late nights in your campervan.

Dometic Freshjet  FJX7 2200 Motorhome Roof Air Conditioner - Features

  • Cooling and Heating Functionality
  • Superior Air Regulation Technology - motorhomes, caravans or campervans can be cooled at a rapid pace.
  • Superior Energy Efficiency - Advanced compressor and Heat Pump technology reduce general power consumption of the device
  • Sleep mode - Fan speed reduces by 80% to minimise noise when in operation
  • Advanced Soft Start Function - quiet and gentle air conditioner start-up
  • Whisper-quiet operation - with its variable compressor speed, the FJX7 operates silently while maintaining the desired temperature, even when fan is at 100%
  • Remote control included as standard
  • Dometic Climate App - utilise the modern functionalities by controlling your roof air conditioner from the convenience of your smartphone
  • Touchscreen functionalities for quick-fix temperature control
  • Clean Air Purify Technology - effectively reduces bacteria, odours and other pollutants to keep your motorhome, caravan or campervan smelling fresh and clean.
  • Outlet fans are adjustable, allowing for individual airflow regulation if desired
  • Optimised Airflow - new low-profile air distribution box with powerful front and back airflow
  • Low-key and compact design makes the Air conditioner a stealthy upgrade to your campervan or motorhome
  • Built-in LEDs for a gentle ambient light
  • Re-usable dust filter, easy for cleaning
  • Exclusive premium design - aerodynamically shaped rooftop with eye catching LED light curve

 

Dometic Freshjet  FJX7 2200 Motorhome Roof Air Conditioner - Specifications

  • External Dimensions (W x H x D): 702 x 225 x 752 mm
  • Required Fuse: 6A
  • Cooling capacity: 2200 watts
  • Heating capacity: 2000 watts
  • Ideal for vehicles up to 7 m in length
  • Roof installation in caravans, motorhomes and recreational vehicles only
  • Owners of motorhomes more than 7 metres long can use two units to create separate climate zones inside the vehicle
  • Black Option SKU: 9600025788
  • White Option SKU: 9105306511
  • Freshjet can easily be retro fitted in replacement of an existing 400 x 400 roof vent (subject to the roof vent location, & roof space for the AC unit), alternatively it can be retro fitted with 400 x 400 roof cut out
  • Ideal for recreational vehicles, the unit can also be operated efficiently on the move with the option of a DC Kit DSP-T 12 (12V) or DSP-T 24 (24V)
  • For full specification and functionality, please see the Dometic Operating Manual available to view under our ‘Download Manual’ tab on the product page before making any purchase
  • ** This product must be installed by a Dometic approved installer, to not do so will affect the warranty on the product.

Product Name: Dometic FreshWell 2000 Under Bench Air Conditioner
Product Description:
The Freshwell 2000 Hideaway Air Conditioner for caravans or motorhomes up to 6 metres long

Brand new for 2013 is the Dometic Freshwell 2000 under bench Caravan and Motorhome air conditioner. The Freshwell 2000 is built to be fitted under bench to save space and be fully concealed. It has the added benefit of no extra roof weight and the external dimensions, drag factor and physical attributes of your vehicle will remain unaffected. The Freshwell 2000 may be small in its size but not in its power as it’s more than capable of creating a perfect climate in a 6 metre Motorhome or Caravan

Other features:

  • As delivered the Freshwell 2000 is designed for stationary use.
  • 1800 watts/6100 btu/h cooling capacity.
  • Power consumption 650 watts/2.8 amps - cooling. 
  • Blower Speeds 3

What do I get?

The Freshwell 2000  air conditioner is ready for mains installation, complete with a hold down kit and remote control sensor and remote control. The Freshwell 2000 under bench air conditioner features a triple air outlet on one corner of the unit, this has a blanking plug included. Using the blanking plug you can select airflow from either the rear or side of the unit or even use all six outlets! Air distribution is normally by flexible ducting.

What else do I need? (see ducting and vents in the right hand column of this page)

Chilled air sent via the ducting to the roof level of your caravan or motorhome for optimum performance. The Dometic Freshwell 2000 air conditioner is possibly one of the easiest methods of installing air conditioning around today!Compact underbench unit where space is at a premium. Product Name: Fiamma F45S Campervan and Motorhome Wall Mount Awning
Product Description:
Fiamma F45S Campervan and Motorhome Wall Mount Awning

The very latest, strongest and much improved version of the well known Fiamma F45 wind out awnings for Motorhomes and Camper vans. Smooth and silent when winding in and out, even silent when travelling, due to the aerodynamic end caps, which are now made in ‘tree resistant’ aluminium!

The Fiamma F45S awning comes in a range of sizes from 1.9 metres to 4.5 metres to suit Campervans, Motorhomes and even Work Vans. The fully waterproof and washable canopy is readily available in Royal Grey and Royal Blue. The front wind out aluminium bar uniquely has two guide grooves to allow the fitting of two different accessories at the same time. The legs which are stored within the front bar, can stand upon the ground, or can be clipped to the motorhomes sidewall. A crank handle is included with the F45S awning. A range of awning extras include a wind and rain blocker front and side panels or a full Privacy Room which allows you to turn this canopy into a full awning for longer stays.

Available Accessories

Our range of add-ons will enhance your camping experience and make your time on the road even more enjoyable.

  • Awning lights: Illuminate your camping area with our bright and energy-efficient LED lights. Perfect for evening gatherings and late-night chats.
  • Side panels: Expand your living space with our durable and waterproof side panels. Keep the bugs out and the comfort in!
  • Groundsheets: Protect your awning from the ground up with our custom-fit groundsheets. Made from heavy-duty materials, they will keep you dry and comfortable.

Awning Brackets

The Fiamma F45s awning brackets are specific mounting brackets designed to securely attach the Fiamma F45s awning to a campervan or motorhome. These brackets are vehicle-specific, meaning that there are different brackets for different types of vehicles, and it's important to choose the correct bracket for your vehicle to ensure proper installation and function of the awning.

The brackets are made from high-quality materials, to ensure durability and long-lasting performance. They are designed to hold the Fiamma F45s awning in place and distribute the weight evenly, preventing any damage to the vehicle or the awning itself.

The Fiamma F45s awning brackets play an essential role in ensuring that the awning operates effectively and safely on your campervan and motorhome.

Product Name: Fiamma F45 Privacy Room Motorhome Awning Enclosure
Product Description:
Fiamma F45 Privacy Room Awning Enclosure

What Do I Get With a Fiamma Privacy Room?

Almost everything to provide you with extra living space for your motorhome! The Privacy room includes Fiamma’s unique ‘Clip System’. This enables a very quick yet strong assembly of the Fiamma F45 Privacy Room to your F45/F65 awning. In every box is the Clip System itself, Two side panels with a window in each one, A front panel which is fitted with a single large window and a plain single door. The windows can all be opened and rolled up like most caravan awnings and each has an insect mesh screen as well.

Other Recommendations For The Fiamma F45 Motorhome Awning

The door can also be rolled up. The side panels have receptors already fitted at the top at the front to attach a Tie Down Kit. This is highly recommended, but not supplied. We also strongly recommend a ‘Skirt’ to cover the gap below the Motorhome floor and ensure a snug wind free room. Both the Skirt and Tie down can be purchased on our Fiamma accessory page.

Product Description:
Fiamma Caravanstore XL Caravan and Motorhome Awning Canopy

The new Fiamma Caravanstore XL Awning Canopy, is the latest version of the popular Caravanstore awning. The XL provides an increased canopy length to 2.50 metres for extra protection from the elements.

Lightweight, uncomplicated design

Designed for caravans but equally suitable on motorhomes, the Fiamma Caravanstore XL Awning Canopy is an easy to use, lightweight yet sturdy bag awning with quick simple manual operation featuring integrated telescopic legs stored in the roller and designed for your convenience.

Featuring Fiamma's latest patented wide roller the Caravanstore XL is easier than ever to roll and unroll whilst leaving the fabric wrinkle free. When attached to your caravan or motorhome, rolling out the Fiamma Caravanstore XL Awning can be completed in less than a minute.

One awning, multiple uses

The Caravanstore XL awning canopy can be installed on practically any flat sided Caravan, Motorhome or Camper Van with an awning rail. In addition the Caravanstore XL boasts a wide a variety of optional extras for added security and comfort such as the Fiamma Privacy rooms featuring their innovative Clip System available for awnings from 280cm to 440cm length.

Fiamma Caravanstore XL Caravan Awning Canopy features:

  • High quality awning material matching the thickness of the Fiamma F45 and F65 awnings
  • Available in either Royal Grey or Royal Blue
  • Easy installation to a caravan or motorhome with awning rail fitted
  • Trouble free manual operation
  • Double guide on the front bar includes two grooves for dual accessory fittings
  • Anti-scratch Reinforced Bag
  • Rubber wall kit for caravan or motorhome protection
  • We can supply awning rail (part 02361-01A), but for collection only.
  • Note to customers in Northern Ireland - unfortunately due to shipping costs we cannot fulfil any orders to Northern Ireland. Any orders placed will be refunded.

Product Description:
Fiamma Caravanstore Zip XL Awning

The Caravanstore ZIP XL is the latest Fiamma have to offer with more extension, more living space and more comfort. The Caravanstore Zip XL canopy and privacy easily join together with Fiamma's sturdy zips allowing for a fast installation.

The Fiamma Caravan Store XL Awning can be used in connection with the Caravanstore Zip Privacy Room. The Fiamma Caravanstore Zip XL Privacy Room is NOT INCLUDED! Purchase Zip XL Privacy Room HERE.

More space with more light!

The Fiamma Caravanstore Zip XL not only benefits from the additional extension compared to the previous Caravanstore Zip, it also benefits from the increased size of the side panels allowing for larger open-able windows with built in mosquito nets providing plenty of light and ventilation on those sunny days and an interchangeable front panel giving the option of positioning the door left or right.

The Fiamma Caravanstore Zip Awning features include:

  • 1x awning (Caravanstore type)
  • The canopy locks into existing awning rail on your Caravan, Campervan or Motorhome
  • Once locked suitable to be left mounted on either Caravan, Campervan or Motor home whilst in transit

*Please note: a Zip Canopy can not accommodate a standard Privacy Room, and a Zip Privacy Room can not be fitted to an ordinary Awning, if you're planning to buy part second hand on eBay etc, please beware*

Note to customers in Northern Ireland - unfortunately due to shipping costs we cannot fulfil any orders to Northern Ireland. Any orders placed will be refunded.

Product Description:
Dometic Air Conditioner DC Kit 1

The Dometic Waeco DC Kit 1 includes a 'soft start' modified inverter and all the wiring required to install in your Leisure Vehicle. Suitable only for the Dometic Freshjet 1100 Air Conditioner, or retrofit to a Dometic CA1000 or Dometic B1100S.

How does it work?

The inverter on this DC Kit  is "Single-Wave-Like" which means it mimics a single AC/DC alternating line of current but is a modified sine wave voltage. (This satisfies most appliances but please do not hesitate to ask for guidance)

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Dometic DC Kit 1 includes;

  • Inverter [single-wave-like output voltage, with mains priority circuit]
  • Remote control including 5m control cable
  • 2 battery cables 16mm² [1.5m long]
  • 230 volt connection cable
  • Charging current distributor with relay
